        ".     Emperor Michael VII  brought Nikephoros, who was now in his early seventies, out of retirement and declared him  kouropalates  and  strategos  of the Anatolic Theme. The title of kouropalates was reserved for esteemed members of the imperial court who were not related to the ruling dynasty, and officially designated him as a high-ranking general; the title of kouropalates was below the rank of  nobilissimus  and two ranks below the title of ": null
    },
